msgid "What Are Events?"
msgstr "What are events?"

#: ../../source/tutorial/04_01_events.md:9
msgid ""
"**Events** are the key to interactive games. They allow your game to "
"respond to user actions such as key presses or mouse movements, and "
"dynamically change the behavior of your actors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/04_01_events.md:12
msgid ""
"**`on_setup()`**: Called at the beginning to initialize and prepare your "
"world."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/04_01_events.md:13
msgid "**`act()`**: Called on every frame to update the world and its actors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/tutorial/04_01_events.md:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are special event methods like **`on_key_pressed`**, "
"**`on_mouse_left`**, or **`on_clicked_left`** to respond to user actions."
msgstr ""
"There are special event methods like **`on_key_pressed`**, "
"**`on_mouse_left`**, or **`on_clicked_left`** to respond to various user "
"actions."

